	<text>
		<body>
				<p><hi rend="underline">32 G</hi></p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>St. Louis</placeName>&#44; <date>May 6&#44; 1857</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear friend&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I don&#39;t know whether you can use the enclosed article<lb/> and I am not hurt in the least&#44; if you tell me it is not suit&#45;<lb/>able.  I feel that I have not looked around with a sufficiently<lb/> searching mind&#44; to make a complete and correct report.  But I<lb/> believe that I have told the truth.  Should you decide to print<lb/> it&#44; then I wish you would correct my bad English.  Although I<lb/> generally do not do it&#44; but in this case you may be at liberty<lb/> to add or leave off as you see fit&#44; for I can readily see the<lb/> lack of better comprehension.  I should have added that for the<lb/> first time I preached here in the German language on <date>Rosh Hashonah</date>.<lb/>  The congregation might have gotten some new members.  The Bavarian<lb/> congregation followed this example at once.  But I don&#39;t want to<lb/> talk about myself nor do I wish to go into details.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In the near future I hope to send you an entirely<lb/> different contribution&#44; which might have more value.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am happy&#44; exceedingly happy that you continue<lb/> the Occident and am only sorry that I cannot do anything to further<lb/> its distribution.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">When you come to <placeName>New York</placeName> I want you to see my Sefarin<lb/> Especially&#44; ask for my Pehad Yitzhak&#44; the great and rare talmudic<lb/> REAL &#40;ANAL.&#41; LEXICON &#40;dictionary&#41;.  Only a few copies are in<lb/> existence and none are sold in book stores.  <persName>Dr. Zunz</persName>&#44; <persName>Sachs</persName> and<lb/> <persName>Rappaport</persName> paid &#36;30. for a copy.  It will greatly assist you in<lb/> your work and you get 50&#37; off the list price.  You need not spend<lb/> a cent and I can in this manner not only pay off my debt&#44; but also<lb/> the &#36;3. for the new subscription of the Occident.  And moreover&#44; I<lb/> would consider it a favor for which I promise to be thankful in<lb/> later years when I&#44; God helping&#44; will find myself in better financial<lb/> circumstances.</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Yours very truly&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">ISIDOR BUSH</persName></p>
				<p>Addressed&#58; <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44; Editor of the Occident&#44; <placeName>Philadelphia&#44; Pa.</placeName></p>
		</body>
